[lm/research/model-footprint] Resolve model footprint and artifact candidates (started)
Measure repository bytes and dtype counts, calculate memory floors, resolve exact revisions, and identify first-party versus community quantizations.
Known 2026-07-17: official FP8 revision c5f5f263bdd5cc134092897864e8905d8fe7b928 has 82,051,854,384 safetensor bytes (76.417 GiB): 80,636,542,976 FP8, 688,319,744 BF16, and 4,921,664 F32 parameters. This is a storage floor, not measured runtime VRAM. Qwen publishes BF16 and FP8; a one-GPU 4-bit artifact is unresolved.
Known 2026-07-19: four community 4-bit quantizations of Qwen3-Next-80B-A3B-Instruct exist, all verified via HF's /api/models/{repo} JSON metadata (ground truth, not inference):
- cyankiwi/Qwen3-Next-80B-A3B-Instruct-AWQ-4bit: safetensors total 83,791,264,000 bytes (I8:150,528 + I32:78,920,024,064 + BF16:4,871,089,408); on-disk usedStorage 49,264,875,838 bytes; format pack-quantized/compressed-tensors, 4-bit.
- RedHatAI/Qwen3-Next-80B-A3B-Instruct-NVFP4: on-disk usedStorage 47,607,840,091 bytes; format nvfp4-pack-quantized/compressed-tensors, 4-bit; sha b6787aea86799bf50a6e98ee61cd9398b5875578; createdAt/lastModified 2025-12-12.
- RESMP-DEV/Qwen3-Next-80B-A3B-Instruct-NVFP4: on-disk usedStorage 47,607,840,091 bytes (same figure as RedHatAI's NVFP4 build -- plausible given identical quant recipe on the identical base model, not yet independently explained); format nvfp4-pack-quantized/compressed-tensors, 4-bit, num_experts 512, num_experts_per_tok 10; sha 847622526019580d433b196a5c928962d7761ce7; createdAt 2025-10-09.
- dazipe/Qwen3-Next-80B-A3B-Instruct-GPTQ-Int4A16: safetensors.parameters I64:14,756 + I32:77,309,411,328 + F16:4,780,899,072, total field 14,444,722,944; on-disk usedStorage 48,278,078,133 bytes; sha 85a28780005de72fd934d00109ed034839bbea26; createdAt 2025-10-29.
Note: HF's safetensors dtype breakdown reports the packed storage dtype (I8/I32/F16/BF16), not the logical bit-width -- the true quantization (4-bit) only appears in config.quantization_config, consistent across all four checkpoints.
Report: checkpoint bytes, runtime-memory unknowns, documented engine/GPU requirements, and candidate handles; do not infer fit from active parameter count.
-> ssm
