[lm/research/vscode-contract] Resolve VS Code provider contract (started)
Extract the current Custom Endpoint request, streaming, tool-calling, credential, token-limit, and agent-mode requirements from pinned first-party docs and focused probes.
Known 2026-07-17: VS Code Custom Endpoint offers Chat Completions, Responses, and Messages API types; agent mode requires tool calling; VS Code discovers and invokes MCP tools.
Known 2026-07-19: The Custom Endpoint provider (vendor: customendpoint, replaces the deprecated "OpenAI Compatible" provider) selects apiType per model: chat-completions | responses | messages, configured in a chatLanguageModels.json file. Per-model fields: id (model id sent to API), name (picker display name), url (full endpoint URL), apiType (optional per-model override of provider default), toolCalling (bool -- required true for the model to appear in the picker at all, and mandatory for agent mode), vision (bool), maxInputTokens + maxOutputTokens (sum defines the context window shown in UI), editTools (optional array: find-replace/multi-find-replace/apply-patch/code-rewrite), thinking (bool), streaming (bool, default true), zeroDataRetentionEnabled (bool -- when true, suppresses previous_response_id in Responses-API requests), supportsReasoningEffort (array of levels, e.g. minimal/low/medium/high -- enables a Thinking Effort picker), reasoningEffortFormat (chat-completions sends top-level reasoning_effort string; responses sends nested reasoning.effort object), requestHeaders (extra HTTP headers; reserved/forbidden headers ignored). Provider-level fields: vendor, name (group display), apiKey, apiType (default), models[].
Known 2026-07-19 (MCP): configured via .vscode/mcp.json (workspace, shareable) or user-profile mcp.json; server entries are either stdio (command + args) or http/url (remote); example config shows both a remote http MCP server and a local stdio server via npx. VS Code auto-discovers tools on server start; first start requires an explicit user trust confirmation. Sandboxing (sandboxEnabled + sandbox.filesystem/network allow-lists) is available for local stdio servers on macOS/Linux only (not Windows) and auto-approves tool calls when active.
Gap not yet closed: neither VS Code docs page states the literal wire-level JSON request/response body shape (message roles, SSE streaming chunk format, tool_call schema on the wire) -- both pages describe configuration/UI flow only. Since apiType values map directly onto OpenAI's Chat Completions API, OpenAI's Responses API, and Anthropic's Messages API by name, the wire contract for each is inferable from those APIs' own published specs, but this inference is not itself confirmed by VS Code's documentation text.
Report: exact fields and observed wire behavior for each candidate API type.
-> ssm
@guidance text/html https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/agent-customization/language-models
@guidance text/html https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/agent-customization/mcp-servers
